      "content": "distractions are just temporary. it's like putting a bandaid on a severed limb. eventually the distraction wears off and you're just left stuck in the same dark room, knowing that nothing actually changes. the entropy doesn't stop. why even keep fighting to stay in a room that's just getting darker and colder?",
